All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
App
The main class for the application.
ContentLineParser
The ContentLineParser class provides an implementation of the LineParser interface that parses a line of text into a map with a single entry.
ContentTxtLoad
A concrete implementation of the Load interface for loading content data from a text file.
Data
Interface representing the operations that can be performed on data.
DataImpl
The Data class provides methods for modifying, saving, checking, and counting occurrences of patterns in file data.
DataProcessing
Interface representing the operations that can be performed for data processing.
DataProcessingImpl
The DataProcessing class provides methods for managing and processing data associated with users.
DataRepository
The DataRepository class implements the Repository interface for managing file data.
Filename
The Filename class represents a filename with an associated unique identifier.
FilenameLineParser
Parses lines of text to extract Filename objects based on a specified regular expression pattern.
FilenameRepository
The FilenameRepository class implements the Repository interface for managing filename data.
FilenameTxtLoad
A concrete implementation of the Load interface for loading Filename data from a text file.
LineParser<T,U>
The LineParser interface defines a contract for parsing a single line of text into a map.
Load<T,U>
The Load interface defines a contract for loading data from a source file.
LoadFromTxt<T,U>
An abstract class that implements the Load interface for loading data from a text file.
Repository<T,U>
The Repository interface provides a method to access a collection of items.
Save<T>
Interface for saving data to a text file.
SaveToTxt<T>
Abstract implementation of the Save interface for saving data to a text file.
StringToTxtSave
Implementation of the Save interface for saving String data to a text file.
Transfer<T,U>
The Transfer interface defines methods for reading and writing data with a specified format.
TxtTransfer<T,U>
The TxtTransfer class implements the Transfer interface for handling text-based data.
User
Represents a user in the system with an ID, login credentials, and user type.
UserLineParser
Parses lines of text to extract User objects based on a specified regex pattern.
UserRepository
The UserRepository class implements the Repository interface for managing user data.
UserTxtLoad
A concrete implementation of the Load interface for loading User data from a text file.
UserType
Enum representing different types of users.
